  "title": "Punjabi Wabi Sabi",
  "description": "Bollywood meets Breaking Bad? What if Saddam Hussein had a love child with Britney Spears? Hilarious storytelling, Punjabi Wabi Sabi is an irreverant, autobiographical and moving stand-up comedy show by Tahina Awan: a middle-aged, delinquent, perverted, first-gen Canadian Muslim woman born in small town BC in the '70s.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Tahina Awan<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Tahina Awan<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Tahina Awan<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Tahina Awan<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Zayd Mia<br/>",
  "website": "https://www.instagram.com/PunjabiWabiSabi",
  "plain_language": "Growing up Gen X isn’t easy. Especially if you’re a Muslim girl in a small BC town, trying to keep it a secret. This one-woman show follows a funny but struggling narrator as she deals with racism, identity, trauma, and being a teenager in the 1980s. Part stand-up, part theatre, it’s a personal and honest story about fighting to be yourself in a world that wants you to fit in. It’s about how we all carry pain, how we’re more alike than we think, and how being a bit messed up might be what makes us human.",
